This is my to-do list so people can see what's planned, what I've done, and also 
get an idea for the state of the game. 

The version of this file will be updated when I finish the batch of what's on the 
to do list. So like everything you see here was added with v.0.0.2 and after
every single thing is done, I will add things to the To-Do section (denoted
below as act 1.) When I do it will be updated to 0.0.3. This version isn't
insignificant. The 0s represent which phase of development the to-do list
is in. First zero is beta, second 0 is alpha, third is pre-alpha (we are here.)

Pre-alpha means the game is still deep in the production stage. Assets like
art, music, animations, tile sets, maps, gui, etc. are still having
their foundations made. Over time, and as we move to alpha (testing unstable
builds to get data and feed back to improve for different hardware and stuff)

Alpha is not really a game release even though it is play testing the 
earliest versions of the game. The point is to make sure the game is stable,
that menus and controls work, and towards the end of alpha will be building 
ontop of the foundations laid in alpha and pre-alpha. 

Beta is most analogous to early access. The core of the game is finished 
and the rest is being fleshed out. Testing complicated systems. Polishing the
game. Beta is the last phase before official release.

