===================[Story Board]====================

Prologue: 
	
   Rolling slides with exposition briefly describing collective belief, integration, 
   meta humanity, and then pivot to a faceless character handed a manilla folder with META 
   clearly written.

  Opening Cut Scene, drone-like footage of Ground City that slowly approaches concrete building
  inside Jennifer with a hardhat and high vis vest, she joins two large SCR wire together,
  electricity arcs and they are soldered together, opening credits roll, Jen clocks out and 
  begins to descend the building

  Tipzl sits at a computer with the monitor obscuring her face below the eyes, blue light 
  reflecting on skin, typing. Her augmented reality glasses with a graph of data playing 
  out right to left over her eye, allowing her to quickly parse data from what she is reading.
  Tipzl looks at the camera and smiles.

  Transitioning to a bar scene with a haze of smoke covers a dimly lit room where dark
  and neon lights illuminate it.

  Contrasted with these happier scenes before the music will dip in pitch and tone showing
  Hatman recieving the manilla folder from an unnamed woman. 
  
  He takes a quick look at it, his eyes scanning the page, and his eyes widen expressing
  concern.
  
  Cross fade transition to Hatman, katana swaying on one side of his hips, and couple of
  guns on the other and a back pack on. He runs through an wet alleyway splashing up water with
  each step. A vial of liquid falls out of his bag and rolls down a street drain. The camera 
  follows it into the undercity. It rolls past several doors before stopping in front of a 
  door with a sign that says Sulfuric Acid. Foreshadowing the water treatment facility the
  players visit in act 3. The door and wall fade and change to an apartment door. 
  Apartment 41.
  
  Music should be somewhat upbeat for beginning of the game but with a quiet sad undertone



